1
00:00:32,658 --> 00:00:35,953
BEHIND EVERY STAR

2
00:01:19,997 --> 00:01:21,832
You were super restless in your sleep.

3
00:01:22,874 --> 00:01:24,167
EPISODE 9

4
00:01:24,251 --> 00:01:25,877
I guess I had a bad dream.

5
00:01:28,422 --> 00:01:29,881
-Shall we?
-Yes.

6
00:01:42,019 --> 00:01:45,147
Then who else will be on the show with me?

7
00:01:45,230 --> 00:01:46,940
The others on the show…

8
00:01:48,483 --> 00:01:49,776
are a secret.

9
00:01:50,444 --> 00:01:52,613
You'll meet them when you get there.

10
00:01:52,696 --> 00:01:55,824
So you really do things like this.
I'm looking forward to it.

11
00:01:56,450 --> 00:01:58,285
Have you watched <i><font color="white">Earth Arcade</font></i>?

12
00:01:58,368 --> 00:02:00,704
Of course, I enjoyed it so much.

13
00:02:00,787 --> 00:02:02,664
It's the hottest program right now.

14
00:02:02,748 --> 00:02:06,627
I never imagined I would
get to be a part of season two.

15
00:02:06,710 --> 00:02:08,587
Where's the location?

16
00:02:08,670 --> 00:02:10,088
The location?

17
00:02:10,172 --> 00:02:12,257
That is also

18
00:02:12,924 --> 00:02:13,884
a secret.

19
00:02:15,427 --> 00:02:17,763
You'll find out at the airport anyway.

20
00:02:18,347 --> 00:02:20,599
And what we're going to do there is…

21
00:02:20,682 --> 00:02:23,352
Also a secret.

22
00:02:24,686 --> 00:02:25,646
Actually,

23
00:02:25,729 --> 00:02:29,983
there is one thing you need to do.

24
00:02:30,067 --> 00:02:31,151
What is it?

25
00:02:31,234 --> 00:02:32,944
And that is…

26
00:02:33,028 --> 00:02:35,447
So you go, then go up…

27
00:02:41,703 --> 00:02:44,706
Joo-ryoung, why did he tell you
to train for rappelling?

28
00:02:44,790 --> 00:02:46,375
-What will he make you do?
-Gosh.

29
00:02:46,458 --> 00:02:48,377
Something like boot camp, probably.

30
00:02:48,460 --> 00:02:50,754
But why do I have to do this with you?

31
00:02:50,837 --> 00:02:53,673
Come on, have you no loyalty?
How can I do this alone?

32
00:02:55,133 --> 00:02:57,094
Joo-ryoung, are you really not scared?

33
00:02:57,177 --> 00:03:01,431
Hey, I went bungee jumping very often
when I was in the US.

34
00:03:01,515 --> 00:03:04,184
Back then, it was much higher than this…

35
00:03:15,695 --> 00:03:17,197
Joo-ryoung, what's wrong?

36
00:03:17,280 --> 00:03:18,365
Right.

37
00:03:20,242 --> 00:03:21,368
It's nothing.

38
00:03:23,787 --> 00:03:24,788
Jung-don.

39
00:03:24,871 --> 00:03:26,039
You can go first for now.

40
00:03:26,123 --> 00:03:27,082
What?

41
00:03:27,165 --> 00:03:28,917
I'll do it later. Untie me now.

42
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:30,210
-What's wrong?
-Joo-ryoung, what is it?

43
00:03:30,293 --> 00:03:32,963
-I need to make a restroom run.
-Restroom.

44
00:03:33,046 --> 00:03:34,423
You went three times already.

45
00:03:34,506 --> 00:03:36,049
-Please make it quick.
-Okay.

46
00:03:36,133 --> 00:03:37,384
-I'll be back.
-Join me after.

47
00:03:37,968 --> 00:03:39,261
-See you.
-Joo-ryoung.

48
00:03:39,344 --> 00:03:41,221
Wait, no.

49
00:03:41,304 --> 00:03:42,264
What?

50
00:03:42,764 --> 00:03:44,099
Prepare for descent!

51
00:03:44,182 --> 00:03:45,726
Good luck.

52
00:03:45,809 --> 00:03:46,893
Descent.

53
00:03:50,147 --> 00:03:51,398
Going down.

54
00:03:52,983 --> 00:03:54,526
Joo-ryoung!

55
00:03:58,947 --> 00:04:01,241
DIRECTOR JANG MYUNG-AEH

56
00:04:03,201 --> 00:04:04,870
Is something going on at work?

57
00:04:06,872 --> 00:04:08,123
No, nothing.

58
00:04:08,665 --> 00:04:11,251
Make sure you go tell him.

59
00:04:11,835 --> 00:04:14,921
If you don't, I'll go over
and turn the place upside down.

60
00:04:15,005 --> 00:04:15,839
Okay.

61
00:04:16,923 --> 00:04:18,133
I'll be back.

62
00:04:23,013 --> 00:04:24,514
Goodness.

63
00:04:42,407 --> 00:04:44,576
-Director Ma.
-Hey.

64
00:04:45,994 --> 00:04:47,579
My mom is here.

65
00:04:49,247 --> 00:04:50,332
Where?

66
00:04:51,416 --> 00:04:52,918
At my place.

67
00:04:53,001 --> 00:04:54,628
She came yesterday.

68
00:04:54,711 --> 00:04:56,046
I see.

69
00:04:57,380 --> 00:05:00,258
I'm eating lunch with her
tomorrow afternoon,

70
00:05:00,342 --> 00:05:03,261
and she asked for you to join
if you have time.

71
00:05:03,345 --> 00:05:05,263
I have a previous engagement tomorrow.

72
00:05:05,347 --> 00:05:06,515
I see.

73
00:05:07,015 --> 00:05:08,433
What about the day after?

74
00:05:08,934 --> 00:05:11,853
The day after? Probably a meeting.

75
00:05:11,937 --> 00:05:15,816
If you don't come,
she said she'll come to the office.

76
00:05:17,067 --> 00:05:19,528
I'll be there tomorrow.
I can push my schedule back.

77
00:05:20,946 --> 00:05:21,988
Okay.

78
00:05:27,327 --> 00:05:30,956
What will happen
to Director Jang Myung-aeh now?

79
00:05:32,207 --> 00:05:34,626
Will she really retire like this?

80
00:05:41,925 --> 00:05:44,094
-We'll take the plants to the warehouse.
-Yes.

81
00:05:44,177 --> 00:05:47,222
We'll use the elevator, so this way.

82
00:05:47,305 --> 00:05:49,683
-Okay.
-Please be careful.

83
00:05:53,436 --> 00:05:55,939
The newbie is tearing the place down.

84
00:05:57,357 --> 00:06:01,236
It's best to stay low
and be quiet in times like these.

85
00:06:01,319 --> 00:06:02,362
Gosh.

86
00:06:10,912 --> 00:06:14,791
Has Director Jang
contacted you separately?

87
00:06:14,874 --> 00:06:16,668
I took over her line of work.

88
00:06:18,128 --> 00:06:20,338
I needed some files from you,
so I sent an email.

89
00:06:20,422 --> 00:06:21,965
Please check those,

90
00:06:23,008 --> 00:06:24,509
and finish it by Monday morning.

91
00:06:24,593 --> 00:06:26,469
Everyone's been working late these days.

92
00:06:26,553 --> 00:06:29,472
We also have tons of work
the president asked us to do.

93
00:06:30,265 --> 00:06:31,266
I see.

94
00:06:32,684 --> 00:06:34,603
Then I'll relay
your exact words to the president.

95
00:06:34,686 --> 00:06:35,729
No.

96
00:06:36,771 --> 00:06:39,649
I'm just sharing the situation.
It's not that I won't do it.

97
00:06:43,737 --> 00:06:46,823
Email me all the files
related to Ko Eun-gyul.

98
00:06:47,490 --> 00:06:49,117
Ko Eun-gyul? Why?

99
00:06:49,743 --> 00:06:50,744
Because I need it.

100
00:06:57,208 --> 00:06:58,543
"Because I need it."

101
00:06:59,252 --> 00:07:00,629
Unbelievable.

102
00:07:01,212 --> 00:07:04,841
Look at how she kicked Director Jang out
and took her office.

103
00:07:04,924 --> 00:07:06,551
Good grief.

104
00:07:08,928 --> 00:07:10,013
But wait.

105
00:07:10,680 --> 00:07:14,267
Why did she single out Eun-gyul
and ask for his file?

106
00:07:19,856 --> 00:07:22,525
The client whom Director Jang
was exclusively in charge of.

107
00:07:22,609 --> 00:07:25,445
They're all calling me
because they can't reach her.

108
00:07:26,112 --> 00:07:28,323
I have to meet them individually
and sort it out,

109
00:07:28,406 --> 00:07:30,742
but I'm really bad at this stuff. Gosh.

110
00:07:32,243 --> 00:07:33,286
Should I do it?

111
00:07:34,996 --> 00:07:36,081
Really?

112
00:07:37,499 --> 00:07:38,458
Aren't you busy?

113
00:07:39,334 --> 00:07:41,419
I'm fine. I'll do it.

114
00:07:41,503 --> 00:07:44,673
Joo-ryoung.
You can't get over this in a few days.

115
00:07:45,298 --> 00:07:48,551
You should be honest with Producer Nah
and tell him you can't do it.

116
00:07:48,635 --> 00:07:51,262
<i><font color="white">Jung-don, I really want to do this.</font></i>

117
00:07:51,972 --> 00:07:55,141
<i><font color="white">It might be because
I wasn't feeling my best that day.</font></i>

118
00:07:57,060 --> 00:07:58,019
Okay, Joo-ryoung.

119
00:07:58,103 --> 00:07:59,938
I'll talk to the trainers again.

120
00:08:01,940 --> 00:08:03,608
Joo A-hyun won't sign with us.

121
00:08:05,235 --> 00:08:07,904
She even got all the terms she wanted.
Why all of a sudden?

122
00:08:07,988 --> 00:08:09,614
She thinks she can't work in Korea.

123
00:08:10,824 --> 00:08:13,868
Man, what do we do?
We worked to get her for a long time.

124
00:08:13,952 --> 00:08:18,248
I went back and forth from Paris
for over a year to get her…

125
00:08:18,832 --> 00:08:19,666
Darn it.

126
00:08:20,500 --> 00:08:22,502
Hey, maybe she heard Kim Ji-hoon's story.

127
00:08:22,585 --> 00:08:25,505
Apparently, the president of Star Media
is spreading rumors

128
00:08:25,588 --> 00:08:27,424
that we took his actor by conning him.

129
00:08:27,507 --> 00:08:28,508
No.

130
00:08:29,551 --> 00:08:30,635
I doubt it.

131
00:08:31,886 --> 00:08:33,054
Damn, that Cho Gi-bong.

132
00:08:33,138 --> 00:08:34,264
Hey, Won-jae.

133
00:08:36,057 --> 00:08:37,142
What?

134
00:08:39,352 --> 00:08:41,771
What's this about
cutting the budget for field work?

135
00:08:41,855 --> 00:08:43,690
We're discussing it now. Close the door.

136
00:08:47,193 --> 00:08:50,989
I heard you're going to cut down
on their food and travel costs.

137
00:08:51,489 --> 00:08:53,700
We should be providing more
for their hard work.

138
00:08:53,783 --> 00:08:55,243
Exactly.

139
00:08:55,326 --> 00:08:57,495
They work hard,
so they should get good rest.

140
00:08:57,579 --> 00:08:59,998
I'm totally fine with
expenses from their job.

141
00:09:00,081 --> 00:09:03,835
But tagging along on
actors' personal matters? That's too much.

142
00:09:03,918 --> 00:09:06,546
It's a part of our job
to manage their personal life.

143
00:09:07,255 --> 00:09:09,132
If something happens when they're alone--

144
00:09:09,215 --> 00:09:11,885
We can think about that when that happens.

145
00:09:11,968 --> 00:09:14,345
Agents tag along
when actors go for a drink

146
00:09:14,429 --> 00:09:17,015
just to wait in the car all night.

147
00:09:17,098 --> 00:09:19,392
Let's not do that. It's too low.

148
00:09:19,476 --> 00:09:21,269
I get what you're saying,

149
00:09:21,352 --> 00:09:24,731
but if you suddenly cut costs,
there will be complaints from the field.

150
00:09:25,815 --> 00:09:28,526
And why wouldn't you
discuss these things with us?

151
00:09:29,027 --> 00:09:31,362
If you keep meddling with the field--

152
00:09:31,446 --> 00:09:32,447
Just…

153
00:09:33,907 --> 00:09:35,617
Leave management up to us.

154
00:09:36,701 --> 00:09:38,995
This line of work
is different from other fields.

155
00:09:39,496 --> 00:09:43,124
Keep this up and
the company won't operate smoothly.

156
00:09:43,208 --> 00:09:46,127
So I should just pump in my money,
and sit around and watch?

157
00:09:47,295 --> 00:09:49,923
No, you don't know the business,
so just leave it to us.

158
00:09:52,801 --> 00:09:54,010
And if I do,

159
00:09:54,677 --> 00:09:56,679
can you cover the tax penalty losses?

160
00:10:01,059 --> 00:10:02,268
Let's do this.

161
00:10:03,436 --> 00:10:07,065
You'll each bring me a significant
achievement within the next week,

162
00:10:07,649 --> 00:10:09,150
then I'll leave the work up to you.

163
00:10:09,776 --> 00:10:11,152
If you don't bring anything,

164
00:10:11,903 --> 00:10:13,822
you will no longer talk back to me.

165
00:10:13,905 --> 00:10:15,240
Are you trying to make a bet--

166
00:10:15,323 --> 00:10:17,534
Let's do that. Sure.

167
00:10:18,243 --> 00:10:19,160
All right.

168
00:10:19,244 --> 00:10:23,164
Also, there are actors
who do nothing after signing with us,

169
00:10:23,248 --> 00:10:25,583
so let's slowly cut off
those contracts too.

170
00:10:26,376 --> 00:10:28,253
Time is money.

171
00:10:28,837 --> 00:10:31,214
Wait a minute. Hey.

172
00:10:33,591 --> 00:10:35,718
Don't worry. He can't do much anyway.

173
00:10:37,470 --> 00:10:39,931
You must have some sort of plan.

174
00:10:42,225 --> 00:10:43,685
Hey, you got…

175
00:10:43,768 --> 00:10:46,688
Mr. Kim, focus on
Kim Joo-ryoung doing well.

176
00:10:46,771 --> 00:10:49,524
You know how everyone is
lined up for Nah Yung-suk's shows.

177
00:10:50,400 --> 00:10:53,528
Nurture a good relationship,
and get more of our actors in his shows.

178
00:10:54,821 --> 00:10:55,905
You said back then that

179
00:10:55,989 --> 00:10:58,449
you don't know the business,
so you'll leave it to us.

180
00:10:58,533 --> 00:11:00,451
Why do you meddle with every little thing?

181
00:11:00,535 --> 00:11:02,287
It's adorable to see you so mad.

182
00:11:07,041 --> 00:11:08,084
Je-suk.

183
00:11:08,626 --> 00:11:11,171
You did all kinds of things
to keep the company together.

184
00:11:11,671 --> 00:11:12,964
What was his name again?

185
00:11:13,673 --> 00:11:15,383
Lee Sang-uk?

186
00:11:16,843 --> 00:11:19,762
I can't believe
you hit on the tax investigator.

187
00:11:22,432 --> 00:11:23,349
Well,

188
00:11:24,350 --> 00:11:26,102
you've been like that since childhood.

189
00:11:26,185 --> 00:11:29,022
You always did what you wanted
no matter what it took.

190
00:11:29,105 --> 00:11:30,815
Ambitious and hate to lose.

191
00:11:35,904 --> 00:11:37,113
Are you going to punch me?

192
00:11:37,697 --> 00:11:39,991
No one would take you
if you get fired for that.

193
00:11:43,328 --> 00:11:45,121
You have an awful rep in this field.

194
00:11:46,247 --> 00:11:47,206
Not getting in?

195
00:11:49,876 --> 00:11:51,294
<i><font color="white">I take off my school uniform…</font></i>

196
00:12:06,142 --> 00:12:09,395
ACTOR CONTRACT REVOCATION AGREEMENT

197
00:12:09,479 --> 00:12:13,775
You're telling me not to make use
of Method's name elsewhere.

198
00:12:16,402 --> 00:12:17,445
I'm sorry.

199
00:12:17,528 --> 00:12:19,781
I heard I'm the last one.

200
00:12:21,115 --> 00:12:24,035
Did everyone else agree to this
without any complaints?

201
00:12:28,706 --> 00:12:31,334
They always send
the underlings to do these things.

202
00:12:33,795 --> 00:12:36,506
I finished watching
<i><font color="white">Rainbow Bridge</font></i> yesterday.

203
00:12:36,589 --> 00:12:38,841
The one you starred in.

204
00:12:38,925 --> 00:12:41,010
I don't have many scenes.

205
00:12:41,552 --> 00:12:43,846
But you played an important role.

206
00:12:44,472 --> 00:12:46,641
And I'm not just saying this.

207
00:12:46,724 --> 00:12:50,311
I really loved your performance in it.

208
00:12:53,064 --> 00:12:55,316
I made it this far
thanks to Director Jang.

209
00:12:55,984 --> 00:13:00,238
Older supporting actors like us
are like kites without strings

210
00:13:00,321 --> 00:13:03,324
unless we have a connection like her.

211
00:13:14,669 --> 00:13:15,837
Mr. Park.

212
00:13:17,380 --> 00:13:18,923
If it's okay with you,

213
00:13:19,841 --> 00:13:22,301
what do you think about
working with a new agent?

214
00:13:24,679 --> 00:13:26,014
That's true.

215
00:13:27,140 --> 00:13:29,892
But can she try one more session?

216
00:13:29,976 --> 00:13:31,644
<i><font color="white">There are safety concerns too.</font></i>

217
00:13:31,728 --> 00:13:33,062
<i><font color="white">If she's in that state,</font></i>

218
00:13:33,146 --> 00:13:35,773
<i><font color="white">it'll be tough for her to get trained
at other places too.</font></i>

219
00:13:35,857 --> 00:13:37,191
Okay, I understand.

220
00:13:38,985 --> 00:13:42,113
Hee-sun, Jin-hyeok told me

221
00:13:42,196 --> 00:13:44,115
that you haven't been auditioning.

222
00:13:44,198 --> 00:13:46,075
Director Ma is such a busy man

223
00:13:46,159 --> 00:13:49,328
that he has no time
for a nameless actor like me.

224
00:13:49,412 --> 00:13:52,999
There's this director
named Oh Hun coming over.

225
00:13:53,082 --> 00:13:54,208
Do you want to meet him?

226
00:13:54,959 --> 00:13:55,835
Oh Hun?

227
00:13:55,918 --> 00:13:58,755
The actor-director, Oh Hun?
Last year's Berlinale awardee?

228
00:13:58,838 --> 00:14:01,090
You're right. He's a close friend.

229
00:14:01,174 --> 00:14:02,508
Hee-sun, come for a second.

230
00:14:03,968 --> 00:14:06,804
He's getting ready for a film,
a musical film.

231
00:14:06,888 --> 00:14:09,265
I told him we have an actress
who can sing very well.

232
00:14:09,348 --> 00:14:10,516
I mean you.

233
00:14:10,600 --> 00:14:13,227
Really? My goodness.

234
00:14:13,311 --> 00:14:14,729
I'm a huge fan of Director Oh.

235
00:14:14,812 --> 00:14:17,315
Well, he's on his way now. Have a seat.

236
00:14:17,398 --> 00:14:18,524
Okay.

237
00:14:20,026 --> 00:14:22,737
All right. Try crossing your legs.

238
00:14:23,446 --> 00:14:24,655
Hand on your chin.

239
00:14:26,908 --> 00:14:28,618
You look like an indie singer. Good.

240
00:14:29,494 --> 00:14:31,579
I'm going to switch the entire ending.

241
00:14:31,662 --> 00:14:36,334
The river doesn't capture everything,
so I'm planning to use the sea.

242
00:14:36,417 --> 00:14:39,212
It's much broader.
You know I like stuff to be big.

243
00:14:39,295 --> 00:14:41,130
Of course, the sea is much better.

244
00:14:41,714 --> 00:14:43,549
She's the one I told you about.

245
00:14:46,094 --> 00:14:49,055
Actress Kang Hee-sun,
singer and an actress.

246
00:14:49,138 --> 00:14:52,517
I thought she'd be perfect for this
as soon as I read your script.

247
00:14:53,267 --> 00:14:55,353
She has the right voice
for a musical film.

248
00:14:55,436 --> 00:14:58,648
My film isn't just a musical film.

249
00:14:59,357 --> 00:15:02,402
It's an erotic musical cinema.

250
00:15:02,485 --> 00:15:04,612
-Grab a seat.
-Sure.

251
00:15:07,573 --> 00:15:08,950
You two look great.

252
00:15:11,744 --> 00:15:12,787
So…

253
00:15:13,955 --> 00:15:16,290
It may be that I'm not aware, but

254
00:15:16,999 --> 00:15:19,210
have you released an album?

255
00:15:20,336 --> 00:15:23,172
I'm not a singer who releases albums.

256
00:15:23,256 --> 00:15:25,675
I mostly sing live on the stage.

257
00:15:25,758 --> 00:15:27,093
I prefer that.

258
00:15:27,176 --> 00:15:30,596
I'm not looking for someone
who has technical skills,

259
00:15:31,264 --> 00:15:33,141
but someone with a unique tone of voice.

260
00:15:35,351 --> 00:15:36,561
Imagine this.

261
00:15:37,186 --> 00:15:39,605
Nature as it was in the beginning.

262
00:15:40,189 --> 00:15:43,734
As deep as the roots of the earth,

263
00:15:44,360 --> 00:15:46,028
yet as light

264
00:15:46,112 --> 00:15:48,489
as a leaf.

265
00:15:49,740 --> 00:15:50,616
Yes, I see.

266
00:15:50,700 --> 00:15:52,201
That thing you like.

267
00:15:54,370 --> 00:15:55,705
That's her voice.

268
00:15:55,788 --> 00:15:58,541
Half air, half moisture.
She moistens your ears--

269
00:15:58,624 --> 00:15:59,500
I'm sorry.

270
00:16:00,710 --> 00:16:03,337
This must be sent quickly,
but I have to leave now.

271
00:16:03,421 --> 00:16:04,839
Give this to the courier later.

272
00:16:06,340 --> 00:16:07,675
I'm in a hurry.

273
00:16:12,013 --> 00:16:13,014
Bye.

274
00:16:13,097 --> 00:16:14,932
Aren't you a signed actress here?

275
00:16:16,225 --> 00:16:17,935
-I am.
-So why is this…

276
00:16:18,019 --> 00:16:19,353
It's method acting.

277
00:16:19,437 --> 00:16:23,024
She's about to go into a reading
for an office drama.

278
00:16:23,107 --> 00:16:24,984
So everyone is helping her prepare.

279
00:16:25,860 --> 00:16:28,404
You're right.
"Give this to the courier later."

280
00:16:28,488 --> 00:16:30,406
That was so smooth.

281
00:16:30,490 --> 00:16:31,949
Everyone loves her.

282
00:16:32,033 --> 00:16:34,035
-Is that so?
-You flatter me.

283
00:16:44,962 --> 00:16:46,339
You've improved a lot.

284
00:16:46,422 --> 00:16:48,591
I'm getting much better with lessons.

285
00:16:49,467 --> 00:16:51,802
-Hey, Director Ma.
-Hello, President Bae.

286
00:16:53,221 --> 00:16:55,598
I've been practicing
to get up to your level.

287
00:16:55,681 --> 00:16:57,433
Goodness, don't be modest.

288
00:16:58,935 --> 00:17:01,312
I've been watching your drama.
People love it.

289
00:17:01,395 --> 00:17:03,356
It's great on the outside,

290
00:17:04,065 --> 00:17:05,274
but the set…

291
00:17:06,943 --> 00:17:10,112
It'd be much easier
if we had an agent like you, right?

292
00:17:10,613 --> 00:17:12,615
It'd be easier to control our actors too.

293
00:17:13,741 --> 00:17:17,286
Then why don't we work together?

294
00:17:17,370 --> 00:17:19,330
Then I can help you out.

295
00:17:20,873 --> 00:17:23,584
Really? Then what can I do for you?

296
00:17:24,210 --> 00:17:27,213
I would love to take part in your work
as a producer.

297
00:17:30,216 --> 00:17:33,052
-How about a drink after practice?
-Sounds great.

298
00:17:33,886 --> 00:17:35,596
-See you soon.
-Sure.

299
00:17:41,435 --> 00:17:43,271
<i><font color="white">Don't mind what happened on that day.</font></i>

300
00:17:50,987 --> 00:17:52,238
-Joo-ryoung.
-Okay.

301
00:17:55,074 --> 00:17:56,951
I gave this a thought.

302
00:17:57,034 --> 00:18:00,788
There's a method called exposure therapy
that's used to treat phobias.

303
00:18:00,871 --> 00:18:04,208
Instead of avoiding your fear,
you expose yourself to it to overcome it.

304
00:18:04,292 --> 00:18:05,543
Let's get in.

305
00:18:05,626 --> 00:18:06,669
-Get in?
-Yes.

306
00:18:11,257 --> 00:18:12,633
How far does this go up?

307
00:18:12,717 --> 00:18:15,011
-Higher than you think.
-Really?

308
00:18:15,094 --> 00:18:16,971
Don't worry. Stay focused.

309
00:18:17,555 --> 00:18:18,806
-You got this.
-I got this.

310
00:18:18,889 --> 00:18:20,266
-You can do this.
-I can.

311
00:18:22,727 --> 00:18:23,811
We're here.

312
00:18:24,937 --> 00:18:26,022
Joo-ryoung.

313
00:18:26,105 --> 00:18:29,108
-Don't back out.
-Hey, I can't do this.

314
00:18:29,191 --> 00:18:30,359
But you came this far.

315
00:18:30,443 --> 00:18:32,778
Joo-ryoung. Think of Nah Yung-suk.

316
00:18:33,696 --> 00:18:35,906
All right. One step at a time.

317
00:18:35,990 --> 00:18:38,117
-It's okay. I'll hold you.
-Don't let go, okay?

318
00:18:38,200 --> 00:18:39,827
One more step.

319
00:18:40,411 --> 00:18:41,245
Joo-ryoung!

320
00:18:41,329 --> 00:18:42,997
No, Joo-ryoung!

321
00:18:43,080 --> 00:18:44,248
-Hold tightly!
-I am!

322
00:18:47,126 --> 00:18:48,794
No, Joo-ryoung!

323
00:18:59,221 --> 00:19:00,765
Gosh, my back.

324
00:19:22,453 --> 00:19:25,247
I was never afraid of such things before.

325
00:19:25,790 --> 00:19:29,335
So why am I suddenly like this?

326
00:19:30,461 --> 00:19:32,421
It must be caused by pressure.

327
00:19:34,840 --> 00:19:36,759
Could you be more specific?

328
00:19:36,842 --> 00:19:39,345
On the set of <i><font color="white">Squid Game</font></i>,

329
00:19:40,012 --> 00:19:43,933
there was a scene
where you fell through the glass bridge.

330
00:19:44,558 --> 00:19:47,728
You wanted to perform so well back then

331
00:19:47,812 --> 00:19:50,856
because it was such an important scene.

332
00:19:50,940 --> 00:19:54,527
The burden from that time
turned into pressure,

333
00:19:54,610 --> 00:19:57,279
and that pressure became trauma,

334
00:19:57,363 --> 00:20:00,783
which makes you freeze up
when faced with a similar situation.

335
00:20:00,866 --> 00:20:06,122
Well, actually,
that was my last scene as Mi-nyeo.

336
00:20:06,872 --> 00:20:09,417
So I thought her story would end nicely

337
00:20:09,500 --> 00:20:13,462
only if I successfully act out
her complicated feelings,

338
00:20:13,546 --> 00:20:15,840
so I did experience such pressure.

339
00:20:15,923 --> 00:20:17,091
On top of that,

340
00:20:17,174 --> 00:20:20,886
I couldn't sleep a wink
the night before the shoot.

341
00:20:20,970 --> 00:20:24,849
Even after I was done with the scene,
I didn't like the end result.

342
00:20:24,932 --> 00:20:28,519
Your dream and the kindness
in your heart not to harm others.

343
00:20:29,645 --> 00:20:33,190
And you knew this was a real chance,
and you had to make the best of it.

344
00:20:33,274 --> 00:20:38,195
You had a tough time physically,
emotionally, and psychologically.

345
00:20:38,279 --> 00:20:40,114
And your body remembers that.

346
00:20:46,537 --> 00:20:49,415
I'd like to take on Mr. Park Chun-bae.

347
00:20:50,708 --> 00:20:51,709
Who's he?

348
00:20:51,792 --> 00:20:53,753
An actor Director Jang used to manage.

349
00:20:53,836 --> 00:20:56,046
He played
lots of supporting roles and extras,

350
00:20:56,130 --> 00:20:57,673
and he recently took up

351
00:20:57,757 --> 00:21:00,509
an important role on a show
called <i><font color="white">Rainbow Bridge</font></i>.

352
00:21:00,593 --> 00:21:02,261
Didn't I tell you to get rid of him?

353
00:21:05,306 --> 00:21:06,932
You probably don't know,

354
00:21:07,016 --> 00:21:09,727
but he's highly respected
in the theater scene.

355
00:21:09,810 --> 00:21:11,771
If we officially sign a contract with him

356
00:21:11,854 --> 00:21:14,148
and pay him a little more attention,

357
00:21:14,231 --> 00:21:16,942
he'll be able to land
much better projects in the future.

358
00:21:19,361 --> 00:21:21,238
If you want to sign actors by talent,

359
00:21:21,322 --> 00:21:23,407
there's a truck full of them
in the theater district.

360
00:21:26,118 --> 00:21:27,077
So what I mean is--

361
00:21:27,828 --> 00:21:29,079
No.

362
00:21:30,331 --> 00:21:31,832
If you want to convince me,

363
00:21:31,916 --> 00:21:35,127
then show me
how he'll benefit this agency.

364
00:21:38,130 --> 00:21:40,549
Ms. Lim is right about that.

365
00:21:41,675 --> 00:21:44,470
Actors with lots of experience
but low public profiles

366
00:21:45,471 --> 00:21:48,516
end up losing us money
once we take out the expenses.

367
00:21:50,017 --> 00:21:53,187
He might not want to sign with us.

368
00:21:54,146 --> 00:21:56,398
He's not paid a lot,
so if he splits it with us,

369
00:21:56,482 --> 00:21:58,234
there's not much left for him.

370
00:21:59,276 --> 00:22:02,154
Money is always the problem, isn't it?

371
00:22:02,905 --> 00:22:05,366
You already have a lot of work.

372
00:22:05,449 --> 00:22:07,576
Why do you make more work for yourself?

373
00:22:08,828 --> 00:22:11,080
Is it to get on the president's good side?

374
00:22:12,122 --> 00:22:13,165
It's not like that.

375
00:22:14,250 --> 00:22:17,127
I'll eat lunch alone today.

376
00:22:22,174 --> 00:22:24,552
Their dishes are out of this world.

377
00:22:25,678 --> 00:22:28,681
-Shall we eat together?
-I'm meeting my mom today.

378
00:22:28,764 --> 00:22:30,099
Enjoy your lunch.

379
00:22:30,182 --> 00:22:31,725
Have a good time then.

380
00:22:33,310 --> 00:22:36,689
Then let's go eat lunch, Eun-soo.

381
00:22:39,817 --> 00:22:40,901
Eun-soo.

382
00:22:41,986 --> 00:22:43,070
Let's go eat.

383
00:22:43,153 --> 00:22:46,365
I brought lunch. You can eat alone.

384
00:22:51,829 --> 00:22:54,206
Please. That's enough.

385
00:22:55,833 --> 00:22:58,502
I need to look younger,
even if it's only a year.

386
00:23:00,379 --> 00:23:02,131
You're killing me.

387
00:23:04,466 --> 00:23:07,094
I'm too hungry. Let's order first.

388
00:23:07,678 --> 00:23:08,596
Excuse me.

389
00:23:09,805 --> 00:23:10,848
He's here.

390
00:23:11,599 --> 00:23:13,767
What is this? Why does he look the same?

391
00:23:13,851 --> 00:23:15,227
You look the same too.

392
00:23:17,354 --> 00:23:19,231
-It's been a while.
-Hey.

393
00:23:19,982 --> 00:23:21,150
You still look rad…

394
00:23:22,568 --> 00:23:23,694
wonderful.

395
00:23:25,529 --> 00:23:27,948
Jeong-hee, you're the same too.
You haven't changed a bit.

396
00:23:31,035 --> 00:23:32,411
You haven't ordered, right?

397
00:23:33,245 --> 00:23:34,371
Excuse me.

398
00:23:36,040 --> 00:23:37,041
Excuse me.

399
00:23:37,124 --> 00:23:38,917
Come take our order.

400
00:23:39,001 --> 00:23:40,002
Mom.

401
00:23:57,519 --> 00:23:58,854
Hello.

402
00:23:58,937 --> 00:24:01,106
I can't seem to reach my husband.

403
00:24:03,859 --> 00:24:06,737
Oh, no. My gosh.

404
00:24:07,446 --> 00:24:08,489
Please pick up.

405
00:24:08,572 --> 00:24:11,742
Director Ma left for lunch
about an hour ago.

406
00:24:12,701 --> 00:24:14,119
Director Ma, it's Eun-soo.

407
00:24:14,203 --> 00:24:16,872
Your wife is at the office. What do I do?

408
00:24:16,955 --> 00:24:18,415
-Oh, no!
-She's over there.

409
00:24:18,499 --> 00:24:20,125
I think she's onto us. What now?

410
00:24:20,209 --> 00:24:21,794
Call me when you hear this.

411
00:24:26,674 --> 00:24:27,758
Eun-soo.

412
00:24:29,218 --> 00:24:30,260
Eun-soo?

413
00:24:31,553 --> 00:24:32,721
I'm sorry.

414
00:24:37,309 --> 00:24:39,937
-Eun-soo.
-I have to hurry out right now.

415
00:24:40,020 --> 00:24:42,106
Do you know where my husband is?

416
00:24:43,440 --> 00:24:45,693
Hee-sun said you would know.

417
00:24:45,776 --> 00:24:47,611
I wouldn't know.

418
00:24:47,695 --> 00:24:49,279
I'm late for lunch right now.

419
00:24:49,363 --> 00:24:53,158
I have to eat with Hyun-joo
and her mother right now.

420
00:24:53,242 --> 00:24:54,827
I'm running late, so I must go.

421
00:24:56,578 --> 00:24:58,455
Hyun-joo's mother?

422
00:24:58,539 --> 00:25:00,666
Yes, she came from Busan yesterday.

423
00:25:00,749 --> 00:25:01,792
Goodbye.

424
00:25:05,254 --> 00:25:06,255
I'll come with you.

425
00:25:08,465 --> 00:25:11,844
I haven't had lunch yet either.

426
00:25:18,183 --> 00:25:20,769
How can you two not say a word to me?

427
00:25:22,187 --> 00:25:23,689
You two are the same.

428
00:25:23,772 --> 00:25:25,983
No, she got her stubbornness from you.

429
00:25:26,066 --> 00:25:28,652
Spending time with her,
I see now how similar you two are.

430
00:25:29,236 --> 00:25:31,447
I really didn't know he was here.

431
00:25:35,325 --> 00:25:36,702
Long time no see, Hyun-joo.

432
00:25:37,828 --> 00:25:39,037
Honey.

433
00:25:39,830 --> 00:25:41,081
Long time no see, Honey.

434
00:25:41,165 --> 00:25:42,374
Well…

435
00:25:45,252 --> 00:25:46,211
Hello.

436
00:25:47,379 --> 00:25:48,589
Hello.

437
00:25:50,382 --> 00:25:52,676
I always wanted a chance to meet you.

438
00:25:52,760 --> 00:25:53,886
My name is Song Eun-ha.

439
00:25:54,636 --> 00:25:56,805
I'm his wife.

440
00:25:58,766 --> 00:26:00,768
My name is So Jeong-hee. Hyun-joo's mom.

441
00:26:00,851 --> 00:26:02,436
Let's talk outside.

442
00:26:08,192 --> 00:26:10,486
Eun-soo, you should go back to the office.

443
00:26:10,569 --> 00:26:13,489
Why are you here? So Ji-sub--

444
00:26:14,740 --> 00:26:16,074
Your dad must be coming.

445
00:26:16,158 --> 00:26:19,286
I'll explain this later.
You should go back.

446
00:26:19,369 --> 00:26:21,371
Is she onto us?

447
00:26:22,039 --> 00:26:23,707
-Is she?
-No, go back.

448
00:26:23,791 --> 00:26:24,875
Go now.

449
00:26:39,264 --> 00:26:41,850
I asked him to meet us.

450
00:26:43,060 --> 00:26:44,728
You don't have to explain, Hyun-joo.

451
00:26:49,107 --> 00:26:50,359
Do you come to Seoul often?

452
00:26:50,943 --> 00:26:53,320
No, I came to meet her.

453
00:26:53,403 --> 00:26:54,947
Otherwise, I wouldn't visit Seoul.

454
00:26:57,658 --> 00:27:01,829
Tae-oh and I last met
when she entered high school,

