00:27:01,912 --> 00:27:03,914
and it's been eight years since then.

456
00:27:10,254 --> 00:27:11,588
When do you go back to Busan?

457
00:27:11,672 --> 00:27:12,965
Before the weekend.

458
00:27:18,554 --> 00:27:19,638
May I have your number?

459
00:27:19,721 --> 00:27:21,598
-Why do you need--
-I'd like to meet you

460
00:27:21,682 --> 00:27:23,141
before you return.

461
00:27:26,603 --> 00:27:27,479
Let's do that.

462
00:27:46,123 --> 00:27:47,124
Excuse me.

463
00:27:49,960 --> 00:27:51,211
A glass of whiskey, please.

464
00:27:51,295 --> 00:27:52,379
-Me too.
-Me too.

465
00:27:53,755 --> 00:27:55,382
Why did you get her number?

466
00:27:55,465 --> 00:27:56,800
Why do you want to meet her?

467
00:27:56,884 --> 00:27:58,844
We have to talk, woman to woman.

468
00:27:59,720 --> 00:28:01,263
How far will you take this?

469
00:28:01,346 --> 00:28:03,348
Wasn't it enough for you to kick me out?

470
00:28:03,432 --> 00:28:05,434
And this isn't fair to Hyun-joo.

471
00:28:07,394 --> 00:28:09,396
Do you think I'm hiding something else?

472
00:28:10,188 --> 00:28:13,400
Or the alimony?
How much more do you want from me?

473
00:28:13,483 --> 00:28:15,277
I didn't take anything from you!

474
00:28:15,360 --> 00:28:17,446
You put our home up for sale
without telling me.

475
00:28:17,529 --> 00:28:19,072
That house is mine.

476
00:28:19,656 --> 00:28:22,618
I paid for the remodeling
and the maintenance.

477
00:28:22,701 --> 00:28:25,662
Unbelievable. I never knew
you were such a petty man.

478
00:28:27,748 --> 00:28:29,499
Why did you come to the office?

479
00:28:30,876 --> 00:28:33,754
To see if my unfaithful husband
is doing well alone.

480
00:28:33,837 --> 00:28:34,671
What now?

481
00:28:37,883 --> 00:28:40,135
Eun-gyul told me you collapsed.

482
00:28:41,053 --> 00:28:43,472
I was an idiot for being worried.

483
00:28:47,059 --> 00:28:48,602
It's really over.

484
00:28:48,685 --> 00:28:51,480
You'll get the divorce papers.
Sign it and send it back.

485
00:28:58,695 --> 00:28:59,696
Man.

486
00:29:01,531 --> 00:29:04,701
I was out of my mind for a moment.

487
00:29:04,785 --> 00:29:08,497
I thought he'd take care of you,
since he's your dad after all.

488
00:29:09,581 --> 00:29:11,166
This is so wrong.

489
00:29:11,250 --> 00:29:13,126
Pack up. You're coming with me.

490
00:29:13,210 --> 00:29:15,754
I'm already having a tough time at work.

491
00:29:15,837 --> 00:29:18,423
-Why are you piling on?
-So just quit!

492
00:29:18,507 --> 00:29:21,260
No one will miss you even if you quit.

493
00:29:21,969 --> 00:29:25,097
Everything you do there
isn't even important.

494
00:29:25,180 --> 00:29:27,683
It's not like
you work with a famous actor.

495
00:29:28,350 --> 00:29:30,060
An actor's career doesn't equal fame.

496
00:29:30,143 --> 00:29:33,480
Even if no one recognizes my work,
even if my work seems petty,

497
00:29:33,563 --> 00:29:34,731
it's important to me.

498
00:29:40,612 --> 00:29:41,530
Hey.

499
00:29:42,114 --> 00:29:45,284
Hee-sun, can you call me a courier?

500
00:30:05,345 --> 00:30:06,388
A-hyun.

501
00:30:07,097 --> 00:30:08,557
What brings you here?

502
00:30:08,640 --> 00:30:10,058
I'm not here to see you, Ms. Chun.

503
00:30:13,061 --> 00:30:14,229
Hyun?

504
00:30:15,439 --> 00:30:18,525
-Hey!
-Hey! What's going on?

505
00:30:19,151 --> 00:30:21,028
-It's been so long!
-Why are you in Korea?

506
00:30:21,111 --> 00:30:23,113
-What's going on?
-It's been so long!

507
00:30:23,822 --> 00:30:25,240
I'm so glad to see you.

508
00:30:25,324 --> 00:30:27,284
How do you two know each other?

509
00:30:27,367 --> 00:30:28,577
When I was in New York,

510
00:30:28,660 --> 00:30:31,288
his company was
a sponsor for my model agency.

511
00:30:33,915 --> 00:30:35,542
He was such a big help.

512
00:30:35,625 --> 00:30:38,045
Why didn't you tell me
that Mr. Koo was the president?

513
00:30:38,128 --> 00:30:39,087
Mr. Koo?

514
00:31:02,110 --> 00:31:03,820
Yes, hello.

515
00:31:03,904 --> 00:31:04,905
Yes.

516
00:31:06,656 --> 00:31:09,409
I'm very sorry, I forgot to call you back.

517
00:31:10,035 --> 00:31:10,952
Yes.

518
00:31:11,953 --> 00:31:13,413
I haven't checked…

519
00:31:13,997 --> 00:31:16,291
I'm sorry. Let me call you back.

520
00:31:22,464 --> 00:31:23,340
A-hyun!

521
00:31:33,558 --> 00:31:35,519
Why didn't you tell us
you knew each other?

522
00:31:36,228 --> 00:31:37,270
You never asked.

523
00:31:38,855 --> 00:31:40,649
Whatever. So will she sign with us?

524
00:31:41,316 --> 00:31:42,275
I didn't ask.

525
00:31:42,818 --> 00:31:43,735
What?

526
00:31:45,654 --> 00:31:47,739
You didn't want me
to meddle in those affairs.

527
00:31:49,157 --> 00:31:52,119
What? You can't do it on your own?
Do you want me to help?

528
00:31:52,202 --> 00:31:54,079
She'll say yes if I ask.

529
00:31:57,582 --> 00:31:59,793
Promise you'll accept me as the president

530
00:31:59,876 --> 00:32:02,629
and follow every decision I make.

531
00:32:03,922 --> 00:32:04,840
Then I'll help.

532
00:32:07,426 --> 00:32:11,388
I thought about why
you were dying to harass me like this.

533
00:32:13,765 --> 00:32:14,933
In the sixth grade,

534
00:32:15,016 --> 00:32:17,477
I took the entire class
to a hamburger place

535
00:32:17,561 --> 00:32:20,105
because I wanted to be
the entertainment officer.

536
00:32:20,730 --> 00:32:22,774
ENTERTAINMENT OFFICER

537
00:32:22,858 --> 00:32:24,734
I want to be the entertainment officer.

538
00:32:25,861 --> 00:32:27,446
Hamburgers are on me, guys.

539
00:32:30,031 --> 00:32:32,242
Je-suk, hamburgers are on me!

540
00:32:32,325 --> 00:32:34,202
-Let's make you the entertainment officer!
<i><font color="white">-Back then,</font></i>

541
00:32:34,286 --> 00:32:35,495
<i><font color="white">you had a crush on me,</font></i>

542
00:32:35,579 --> 00:32:38,165
<i><font color="white">so you said you'd buy everything
when I didn't even ask.</font></i>

543
00:32:39,124 --> 00:32:42,627
<i><font color="white">You made a whole speech
about how your parents ran the place.</font></i>

544
00:32:43,253 --> 00:32:46,590
<i><font color="white">You began to wail and throw a fit
when you found out I liked someone else.</font></i>

545
00:32:47,257 --> 00:32:48,550
<i><font color="white">-Goodness.</font></i>
-I like you.

546
00:32:49,134 --> 00:32:50,635
Be my boyfriend.

547
00:32:55,557 --> 00:32:57,642
You haven't changed a bit since then.

548
00:32:58,602 --> 00:33:01,396
A kid who's dying for attention.

549
00:33:03,482 --> 00:33:05,609
I'll take care of Joo A-hyun.
Mind your own.

550
00:33:05,692 --> 00:33:06,818
And also,

551
00:33:08,069 --> 00:33:11,490
do you want people to acknowledge you?
Then start acting like a grown-up.

552
00:33:12,032 --> 00:33:14,201
Stop harassing others
while demanding attention.

553
00:33:27,172 --> 00:33:29,925
<i><font color="white">We have an announcement.</font></i>

554
00:33:30,008 --> 00:33:31,092
<i><font color="white">This Sunday,</font></i>

555
00:33:31,176 --> 00:33:35,847
<i><font color="white">President Koo Hae-jun will hold
a magnificent inauguration ceremony.</font></i>

556
00:33:35,931 --> 00:33:38,600
<i><font color="white">Please come and take part.</font></i>

557
00:33:38,683 --> 00:33:40,185
<i><font color="white">Let me repeat.</font></i>

558
00:33:40,268 --> 00:33:41,561
<i><font color="white">This Sunday,</font></i>

559
00:33:41,645 --> 00:33:45,065
President Koo Hae-jun will hold
a magnificent appointment…

560
00:33:47,108 --> 00:33:49,069
I'm going to invite directors, writers,

561
00:33:49,152 --> 00:33:51,321
and everyone that works in broadcasting.

562
00:33:51,404 --> 00:33:54,741
If you're busy, don't come.
But if you have time, join me as you like.

563
00:33:55,325 --> 00:33:56,368
Over.

564
00:34:03,625 --> 00:34:05,210
I'll show you what I'm capable of.

565
00:34:07,087 --> 00:34:08,129
What?

566
00:34:08,797 --> 00:34:09,839
What did he say?

567
00:34:14,010 --> 00:34:15,971
He said come if you like.

568
00:34:17,430 --> 00:34:19,140
It means we don't have to go, right?

569
00:34:19,891 --> 00:34:23,311
I bet my entire fortune that
he'll harass you for life if you don't.

570
00:34:25,522 --> 00:34:27,732
How can he want an inauguration ceremony

571
00:34:28,400 --> 00:34:30,402
after what he did to Director Jang?

572
00:34:30,485 --> 00:34:32,779
Really, it's awful.

573
00:34:32,862 --> 00:34:34,906
Let's boycott the ceremony, everyone.

574
00:34:34,990 --> 00:34:35,991
What?

575
00:34:36,491 --> 00:34:39,619
We can't stand back and just watch him
run the company however he wants.

576
00:34:39,703 --> 00:34:43,790
We should have done something
when Director Jang was dismissed.

577
00:34:44,749 --> 00:34:45,834
Darn it.

578
00:34:47,294 --> 00:34:48,628
Now,

579
00:34:48,712 --> 00:34:51,840
it's not too late to show him.
Let's all boycott the ceremony.

580
00:34:52,549 --> 00:34:54,009
He can try without his staff.

581
00:34:54,092 --> 00:34:55,844
What if he fires all of us?

582
00:34:55,927 --> 00:34:57,470
Then we can all leave.

583
00:34:58,054 --> 00:35:01,600
If we all leave at once,
we aren't the ones who'll be sorry.

584
00:35:01,683 --> 00:35:02,892
It's Koo Hae-jun.

585
00:35:03,435 --> 00:35:06,605
Then we'll be able to bring
Director Jang back too.

586
00:35:07,147 --> 00:35:08,398
Yes.

587
00:35:08,481 --> 00:35:11,234
And above all,
we have Director Ma with us.

588
00:35:14,487 --> 00:35:16,573
You told President Koo

589
00:35:16,656 --> 00:35:18,325
<i><font color="white">to leave management up to you.</font></i>

590
00:35:18,408 --> 00:35:20,785
That he shouldn't harass us anymore.

591
00:35:20,869 --> 00:35:22,078
No, that's because…

592
00:35:22,162 --> 00:35:24,331
Please take the lead once again.

593
00:35:24,414 --> 00:35:26,791
It'll be such great motivation for us
if you do.

594
00:35:31,921 --> 00:35:32,964
Man.

595
00:35:34,049 --> 00:35:35,842
Okay, fine.

596
00:35:38,261 --> 00:35:39,262
Let's make a promise.

597
00:35:39,846 --> 00:35:41,848
We're boycotting
the inauguration ceremony.

598
00:35:41,931 --> 00:35:42,974
Okay.

599
00:35:55,362 --> 00:35:57,697
Gosh, fine. All right.

600
00:35:58,365 --> 00:35:59,407
Gosh.

601
00:36:01,034 --> 00:36:03,953
It's betrayal if you go to the ceremony.

602
00:36:15,340 --> 00:36:17,509
INAUGURATION D-1

603
00:36:17,592 --> 00:36:18,802
Hello.

604
00:36:20,178 --> 00:36:21,221
Any updates?

605
00:36:22,472 --> 00:36:25,058
